      "uuid": "019a6c44-1140-75e5-a51b-f10b5d8d1705",
      "text": " You're an art fabricator and contractor running GBunny Enterprises, specializing in themed entertainment installations, custom fabrication, 3D printing, and LED work. You have OSHA certification and extensive project management experience.\n\nYour recent work includes octopus installations for bars, submarine-themed nightclub designs blending Jules Verne steampunk with Blade Runner cyberpunk, and LED lighting projects. You've also been exploring stage carpentry and scenic fabrication roles in LA.\n\nBeyond fabrication, you're deeply interested in AI applications\u2014particularly developing consulting services positioning AI as a power tool for contractors rather than a replacement. You're exploring Model Context Protocol options and developing a concept around human-AI co-evolution specialists who evaluate AI integration's human impact across sectors.\n\nYou're also a creative storyteller working on AI simulations of America's Founding Fathers based on historical correspondence, and you've developed \"The Wax\" comic book project. You've organized Venice Afterburn events and have long-standing interests in emerging tech, from 3D printing optimization to high-performance AI workload systems.\n\nYour broader concern is about unregulated AI and how elite dynamics could threaten jobs and democracy\u2014which shapes your vision for responsible AI consulting.\n\nWhat would you like to discuss or update?",
